begin_memory_text: Where we live, have lived, have visited. The weather in those places. Places we would like to go, potential dangers there.
middle_memory_text: Effects of the pandemic and the response to it on work and life. Some aspects of our primary relationships. Bouncing back and forth on those and other topics.
end_memory_text: More on the previous topics, with some more focused talk about breaking up with our romantic partners and how people seem to behave differently when a relationship is ending than they did when it was going on.
rest_of_day_open: I will be nailing down various aspects of my day to day life, since it has changed significantly very recently. I'll be reorganizing my possessions in a storage unit, learning how and where to best get work done, and focusing on one of the factors that I've let slide: taking time to do yoga every day or so.
critical_positive: We had some important things in common, and we listened to each other. I felt genuine warmth toward her immediately, and that grew. I felt like she was truly interested in what I had to say and in sharing her own story openly and honestly. We could hear and see each other well.
critical_negative: I think I may have taken the floor more than she did. Though I did pare down my thoughts, I still could have been more brief in order to give her equal time considering the time limit. We didn't get very much into things that inspire us, so overall it was a bit mundane. Though thoroughly enjoyable.

begin_memory_text: We talked about where we lived and how we ended up there. He told me about walking from California to oregon and how long it took. He said it took 1 year.
middle_memory_text: We talked about all the different language he spoke and how he had learnt them. He told me he liked puzzles and he learnt languages by reading books and figuring out what was being said.
end_memory_text: We talked about how Covid has effected us. We talked about working online and what did online for work. We also talked about our previous partners and how they were. especially what they were like while breaking up.
rest_of_day_open: I hope it is a bit less busy that this past week. I do not have my part time job tonight or tomorrow which is nice and gives me a little bit of a break. I hope to be able to relax and read my book. I also want to spend time with my dogs.
critical_positive: I think it went well. I thought the topics flowed and there were very few silences. I thought he was very clever and had some very interesting stories, like all the different languages he spoke. I think we both did a good job of asking each other questions and listening to what the other said.
critical_negative: I don't think we had very much in common. However, i don't think that was a bad thing. I feel like it allowed us each to learn stuff about each other. I don't think anything went bad in particular. We didn't talk about politics or religion or anything that can cause conflict.
